                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/6308: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan (<persName type="from"
                        >Grew</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-05-23T20:00:00+09:00"
                            >May 23, 1933—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 23—8:02 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>105. I have just been told by what is believed to be a reliable source that
                    instructions have been sent to the Japanese troops in North China not to enter
                    Peiping and that in case of any tendency to break in, another more drastic order
                    to the same effect is in readiness.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
